caption: (Translated by Google) I love the service, the teas and shakes 😋😋😋😋😋😋 if you are in Chicago and want something healthy, this is the place for you!  (Original) Me encana el servicio, los teas and shakes 😋😋😋😋😋😋 si andas en chicago y quieres algo healthy que s te es el lugar para ti!
Love love love this place. They are so sweet when you walk in and make you feel so welcome, and the shakes & teas are DELICIOUS.

Mira was so kind from the moment I opened the door. She went over the entire menu with me and even made suggestions based on flavors I liked. She was incredibly kind and overall the vibes were so positive. Thanks for a great smoothie and the sprinkles of happiness!! 🥰

I love the energy at Rise up; shakes and read are amazing and taste good! I have been drinking there shakes for months now and I feel the difference; I recommend that people go try their delicious and nutritious shake!

Front for Herbalife that apparently (see below) keeps 'records' of who visits their shop. Pretty creepy if you ask me.  EDIT: So what if I live in the UK? Both the things I stated are true. Your customers have seen you mixing Herbalife powders instead of making the drinks yourself from scratch, and you yourself claimed to have 'records' of your customers. All I did was state substantiated fact.  As for stopping by for a smoothie some day, I couldn't possibly. No, literally, because you don't make smoothies. You just mix powder with water or milk and charge people money for it.

This store is a front for a Pyramid scheme.  Reply: Where I live is irrelevant, the fact you went out your way to figure out is pretty creepy if you ask me.  Regardless, supporting a pyramid scheme's predatory practices is pretty deserving of a 1 star. Nice to see you also changed your reply to someone else when you were called out for being a weirdo who keeps records of who visits.

This is a front for the MLM Herbalife. MLMs (aka pyramid schemes) are super predatory and problematic, so if you have an issue with this or want to actually support a small businesses in the community spend your money elsewhere.
Did not realize this was an MLM.
WARNING - MLM front. If you want marked up Herbalife products, shop away.
Love this place! So welcoming & great energy! The shakes & teas are so good. I'll definitely be coming back here!

I love the shakes but the teas stole my heart! The shakes keep me full for a couple hours and taste like ice cream and the teas give me SO much energy with out the sugar and without the crash. I love the drinks and the owners are so kind. I highly recommend you stop by and experience the positive energy.
Obsessed with the shakes. Lovely owners as well!
Always love coming to Rise Up!! Great staff and incredible smoothies!! I always leave feeling better than ever :)

Could not agree more with the one star review. Went with my girlfriend and $20 later we had two of the worst tasting smoothies either of us have ever had. Not an exaggeration - tasted so artificial and still grainy with whatever “healthy” powders/shots they up-charged for. Thought the health claims meant real fruits/veggies/dairy/sweeteners but turns out it means weird, powdered, artificially flavored junk. Maybe we got an abnormally bad batch (strawberry cheesecake and cookie dough were the flavors) but that’s even worse because we followed their recommendations. Definitely not the spot if you’re looking for a good fresh fruit smoothie. Bonus star because they were at least friendly while serving up the smoothies.

This place is a scam. Their menu is extremely confusing & overpriced. You may think you’re paying $5 for a protein coffee, when in reality your total will be $10. It’s not like the products are that good, it’s extremely subpar.

I would give rise up nutrition 10 stars if it was possible!! We absolutely love this place. We're from Oak Brook IL but I drive my family down there at least once a week mostly on Sunday's, we've made it a weekly family tradition!! My daughter loves the Oreo smoothie,  she would have one every day if we lived closer. We really like the spicy mango, thats the bomb!! And everyone at rise up is super cool and very nice, the customer service alone should get 10 stars!! Everyone should go get a smoothie especially on those hot Chicago summer days!! 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

Rise Up Nutrition is amazing! I had a tea + smoothie combo and it was soooo good! I highly recommend the Fruity Pebbles smoothie it was super yummy and refreshing.  The staff at Rise Up is really friendly and they do a great job explaining the menu! They also are great at helping you narrow down the perfect drink choice to match your flavor preferences. Seriously check this place out! You won’t regret it.
An exceptional juice experience. Good juice, good tea, good business 🙏🏻

First time trying Rise Up and I couldn’t be more pleased! Friendly curbside pickup (during quarantine shelter in place) and the TASTIEST smoothie. I ordered the teddy graham at Mina’s (sp?) recommendation and keep thinking to myself... wait this is good for me?! Obviously I loved it because I couldn’t help but drink half of it before snapping a pic. 11/10. Will be back!
We received drinks from here at University of Chicago two days ago and it was soooooo good.

I love Rise Up Nutrition! Their shakes and teas are divine! Lately I am obsessed with the Strawberry Chocolate Shake...it is gorgeous and so delicious...this is a great alternative to Starrbucks! You will be glad you stopped in! Friendly lovely people...greet you as you walk in the door..it is my second home!
Amazing customer service!! Definitely recommend if you need a drink that’s rich in protein.
The Cinnamon Toast Crunch smoothie was great. Good vibes and great energy. Good spot to chill

Definitely the spot to be in Lakeview east, great energy. I always feel great after a smoothie and Tea. They also have really good post workout which helps make it easy for me walking home and grabbing it
Great spot to hang out, great energy and good vibes . . Favorite combo is captain America tea and teddy graham ( taste like a cinnamon roll) delicious 😋 I bring all my friends here

Jay and Meera's shop is amazing and full of heart. Rise Up Nutrition brings community together by collaborating with other small businesses for the betterment of their customers. They hope to promote an active, health-conscious lifestyle. They are wonderfully optimistic and stay actively involved in the community. My favorite beverage is Abuelita's Hot Chocolate for comfort and my favorite smoothie is the Smores. Jay, Meera, and their dynamic shop are an asset to Lakeview!

The owner is super sweet and everything I had was Absolutely delicious! Be careful with anything energizing though, the teas are really potent and I would recommend only drinking early in the day, I had it early evening and wasn't able to sleep that night at all! So this os great if you're looking for a real energy boost! The smoothie was filling and a great meal replacement. Will be back!
Great place to grab a nutrition smoothie that will keep you full 4 hours. I love their tea! And The Vibes are very positive and the customer service is great and very friendly.

Utterly fantastic and healthy. Almost too-good-to-be-true. I'm reminded of the Seinfeld episode where they eat frozen yogurt and gain 20lbs. I hope that doesn't happen to me, as I'll be coming back over and over again.  Get the ButterBeer.
Love this place! Just found it yesterday and I'm so upset I didn't find it sooner. They offer so many dairy free options - the frosted animal cookie is so good! All of the employees are so nice.
Cookie dough shake rocked!
So delicious so nutritious
Fantastic place! Shake and Tea combo were great. Highly recommend.

Great place to get a protein shake on the go! most friendly staff in town! Love Meera, Bria, and Jay. You guys rock. They are very motivated to keep you healthy and even offer motivational and workout challenges. If you need a pick me up they have natural teas and protein coffee for that as well. Protein shakes can be dull and chalky tasting but the shakes they offer are great in flavor and smooth. I especially love "mint to be" and "S'mores". Def make your way here and check them out for yourselves :) cheers to your new store and thank you for your awesome service!
